text.tspan: On Wed, 13/03/2019, I mistakenly went to Chiswick, the work location for the
Fri, 15/03/2019. I had to take a trip to return to the actual workplace in
Co-operative Group Food Limited 38 The Broadway Thames Ditton - Surrey KT7 0JW
For this mistake I disclaim the cost for that trip and only claim for tickets
which I brought on the way back home. I was charged by the station's
ticketman £3.20 for the morning trip and £5.60 for the return trip,
as shown in attached tickets. So for this day, I only claim:
£03.20 train fare for the going to workplace
£05.60 train fare for the going back home
